                        <persName ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/95224252" xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Sharaf al-Dīn ʻAlī Yazdī, d. 858/1454</persName>
                        <persName ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/95224252" xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="Standard">شرف الدین علی یزدی</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20110" change="#ids-cleanup">Ẓafarnāmah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_20110" change="#ids-cleanup">ظفنامه</title>
                     <note>The celebrated history of <persName key="person_63984707" role="subject" change="#role-assignment">Timūr</persName> (771-807/1370-1404) and <persName key="person_f1865" role="subject" change="#role-assignment">Khalīl Sulṭān</persName> (807-814/1404-1411), completed first by <persName key="person_f1545" role="ant" change="#role-assignment">Ibrāhīm Sulṭan</persName>, and then elaborated into his final form by Yazdī
                     </note>
                     <note>This copy has been transcribed only four years after the author’s death: it is preceded by the Iftitāḥ or Muqaddimah, a genealogical account of the Turkish Khāns with the history of <persName key="person_100172770" role="oth" change="#role-assignment">Chingīz Khān</persName> and his successors by <persName key="person_95224252" role="aut" change="#role-assignment">Sharaf al-Dīn</persName> in <date when="1419" calendar="#Hijri-qamari">822</date>
                     </note>
                     <note>Completed in <date notBefore="1424" notAfter="1425" calendar="#Hijri-qamari">828</date>
                     </note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>For a more detailed description see , .</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
